This presidential memorandum, issued on April 28, 2020, outlines the policy of the United States to provide federal support to state governors in their responses to threats and hazards, particularly in relation to the COVID-19 pandemic. The memorandum directs the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to fund 100 percent of emergency assistance activities in North Dakota that are carried out by the National Guard. It also directs the Secretary of Defense to request the Governor of North Dakota to deploy National Guard forces on a reimbursable basis to support state and local emergency assistance efforts. The memorandum specifies that the 100 percent federal cost share for North Dakota's use of National Guard forces will be available until May 31, 2020. The memorandum includes general provisions to ensure its implementation is consistent with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations.